The paper studies a game-theoretic model of multi-armed bandit learning with two players, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also uses the Gittins index, which is a well-known algorithm in the field of Multi-Armed Bandits (cs.MA) and explores the tradeoff between exploration and exploitation, which is a common theme in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
